     629:      * We call the label manager here to define a name for the new
     630:      * segment, and when our _own_ label-definition stub gets
     631:      * called in return, it should register the new segment name
     632:      * using the pointer it gets passed. That way we save memory,
     633:      * by sponging off the label manager.
     634:      */
